{"id":90555,"title":"Myocardial infarction due to lightning strike.","abstract":"Cardiac events due to lightning strike and their severity vary according to the strength of the electric current and the duration of exposure. The electrophysiological effects of lightning on the heart can result in ventricular fibrillation, asystole, QT prolongation, supraventricular tachycardia, and non-specific ST-T wave changes. In this report, a case of a patient who suffered myocardial infarction due to lightning strike is presented, which is a rare complication.","date":"2014-03-07","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24601203","annotations":[{"name":"Supraventricular tachycardia","weight":0.877494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supraventricular_tachycardia"},{"name":"Myocardial infarction","weight":0.850122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myocardial_infarction"},{"name":"Tachycardia","weight":0.810695,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tachycardia"},{"name":"Ventricular fibrillation","weight":0.80973,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ventricular_fibrillation"},{"name":"Asystole","weight":0.762063,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asystole"},{"name":"Electrophysiology","weight":0.751564,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrophysiology"},{"name":"Cardiac muscle","weight":0.743484,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiac_muscle"},{"name":"Ventricle (heart)","weight":0.723778,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ventricle_(heart)"},{"name":"Heart","weight":0.689867,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart"},{"name":"Long QT syndrome","weight":0.660996,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_QT_syndrome"},{"name":"Hypothermia","weight":0.536506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypothermia"},{"name":"Electric current","weight":0.374497,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electric_current"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Infarction","weight":0.221662,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infarction"},{"name":"Fibrillation","weight":0.13506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibrillation"},{"name":"Lightning","weight":0.124446,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lightning"},{"name":"QT interval","weight":0.067811,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QT_interval"},{"name":"Electricity","weight":0.018953,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electricity"},{"name":"Half-life","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Half-life"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Wave","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wave"}]}
